.TH "adis_single_conversion" 9 "adis_single_conversion" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adis_single_conversion \- Performs a single sample conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" adis_single_conversion
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ","
.BI "const struct iio_chan_spec *chan "  ","
.BI "unsigned int error_mask "  ","
.BI "int *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
The IIO device
.IP "chan" 12
The IIO channel
.IP "error_mask" 12
Mask for the error bit
.IP "val" 12
Result of the conversion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns IIO_VAL_INT on success, a negative error code otherwise.

The function performs a single conversion on a given channel and post
processes the value accordingly to the channel spec. If a error_mask is given
the function will check if the mask is set in the returned raw value. If it
is set the function will perform a self-check. If the device does not report
a error bit in the channels raw value set error_mask to 0.
